<a id="top"> </a><h1>Associate Professor in Philosophy of Science, University of Geneva</h1>
<p>
The University of Geneva's Department of Philosophy has an 
open faculty position for Associate Professor (60%) in 
Philosophy of Science. Teaching load: 3.5 courses per year. 
Further details can be found <a href="https://jobs.icams.unige.ch/www/wd_portal.show_job?p_web_site_id=1&amp;p_web_page_id=12952" rel="external">here</a>. 
Teaching at the Department of Philosophy is for the most 
part in French. New faculty are required to be able to 
teach in French no later than one year after their 
appointment. Informal inquiries may be directed to Prof. 
Marcel Weber (<a href="mailto:marcel.weber@unige.ch" rel="email">marcel.weber@unige.ch</a>)
</p>
